{"word":"πορεύω","slug":"πορεύω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>πορεύω</b></el> <br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:πόρος'><el>πόρος</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>Act.</a></a> <i>to make to go, carry, convey</i>, <b><a href='S:Pindar'>Pind.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> dupl. <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to carry</i> or <i>ferry over</i>, <el>Νέσσος ποταμὸν βροτοὺς ἐπόρευσε</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>; <el>γυναῖκ' λίμναν πορεύσας</el> <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of things, <i>to bring, furnish, bestow, find</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a> and <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>Mid.</a> <i>to be driven</i> or <i>carried</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to go, walk, march</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; <i>to go across, pass</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to enter</i>, <el>π. στέγας</el> <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> cogn., <el>μακρὰν ὁδὸν π.</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> loci, <i>to go over, traverse</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>to walk</i>, <a href='S:id est'>i. e.</a> <i>live</i>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}